cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Waddl: AI coding assistance that supports learning"
message: "If you use Waddl in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Carissa
    family-names: Ott
    email: carissaott0809@gmail.com
abstract: >-
  Waddl is an open-source research project exploring how AI coding tools
  can support problem-solving without replacing the thinking that helps
  people learn. It develops and evaluates interaction patterns such as
  adaptive hints, self-explanation prompts, assistance fading, and
  reflection checkpoints, delivered inside a real coding workflow via a
  Claude Code plugin.
keywords:
  - learning sciences
  - developer tools
  - human-computer interaction
  - AI coding assistants
  - desirable difficulties
  - scaffolding
license: Apache-2.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/carissamercedesott/waddl"
url: "https://github.com/carissamercedesott/waddl"
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-07-23"
